  "body": "View this post on the web at https://www.commonreader.co.uk/p/the-whitsun-weddings-philip-larkin\r\n\r\nI knew ‘The Whitsun Weddings’ very well, but memorisation has made me appreciate the way Larkin makes his pastoral out of sound and form, as well as image; I also understood the presence of death more clearly. And I thought I heard the influence of Eliot and Gray, as well as the more apparent Keats and Tennyson. You can watch this recitation here or on YouTube [ https://substack.com/redirect/e5f7a380-1a48-4c25-b24d-3198329c055d?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8 ]. The poem is available on Poetry Foundation [ https://substack.com/redirect/ba6f66c5-a1ea-4bc4-a102-93c5eefc8e0c?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8 ].\r\n\r\nUnsubscribe https://substack..J4lF_XvNQdrT-5m-krQ4w-CMx9MI82pplECb16jxfMQ?",
